From 19aa11c44071a50cc68d0dd2bf4eb78b552c8826 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Timon Sassor <timon.sassor@governikus.de>
Date: Tue, 14 Oct 2025 17:26:26 +0200
Subject: a11y Android: Implement granular text navigation and selection

TalkBack allows it to change the text navigation on editable components
between character, word, line, sentence etc.. Additionally you can
enable a selection mode, which then moves the cursor and selects text by
that granularity.
To achieve this, the Android Platform plug-in now listens to these
gestures, passes them to editable components like TextInput and emits the
appropriate events to TalkBack.

[ChangeLog][Accessibility][Android] Enable granular text navigation
and selection for editable components e.g. TextInput

Fixes: QTBUG-139943
Change-Id: I118222bc23c192d3bc9198f639166f39801691e8
